<div class="home-bio">
  <p>Michael Lenczner has spent two decades at the intersection of technology and social change — founding initiatives in the community wireless and open data movements, and working across governments, funders, and nonprofits. He is the founder and CEO of DARO, a consulting firm that helps mission-driven organizations navigate change and have more impact. He is also a School Fellow at Carleton University's School of Public Policy and Administration.</p>
